article.description: — Avery Anderson had 18 points, Moussa Cisse had a double-double, and Oklahoma State defeated Oakland 91-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: Anderson, Cisse power Oklahoma State past Oakland 91-62
article.linkText: Anderson, Cisse power Oklahoma State past Oakland 91-62
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- — Avery Anderson had 18 points, Moussa Cisse had a double-double, and Oklahoma State defeated Oakland 91-62 on Sunday. Caleb Asberry made two 3-pointers and a pair of free throws in a 14-2 second-half run that put the Cowboys in control, 58-35, with 12:30 remaining. Asberry scored 13 points in 21 minutes of play off the bench. Four players combined to score 33 bench points. John-Michael Wright had 16 points, including 4-of-7 3-pointers, for the Cowboys. Cisse had 11 points and 10 rebounds and Anderson added seven of Oklahoma State's 24 assists. The Cowboys' 12 3-pointers in 23 attempts marked their most 3-point makes since February of 2021. Oakland, which upset the Cowboys in Stillwater, Oklahoma, last year, also had four players score in double-figures. Keaton Hervey had 15 points and 11 rebounds, Trey Townsend scored 12 points and Blake Lampman added 10 points. Lorne Bowman scored 14 of the Golden Grizzlies' 18 bench points. Runs of 11-0 and 11-2 in the first half helped the Cowboys take a 41-27 lead at halftime. ------
